#: ../../C/computer-confetti.rst:5
msgid "computer confetti"
msgstr "computer confetti"

#: ../../C/computer-confetti.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../C/computer-confetti.rst:9
msgid ""
"Syn. :ref:`chad`\\. [obs.] Though this term was common at one time, this use"
" of punched-card chad is not a good idea, as the pieces are stiff and have "
"sharp corners that could injure the eyes. GLS reports that he once attended "
"a wedding at MIT during which he and a few other guests enthusiastically "
"threw chad instead of rice. The groom later grumbled that he and his bride "
"had spent most of the evening trying to get the stuff out of their hair."
msgstr ""
"\\ :ref:`chad`\\ と同義。[廃語] "
"この用語はかつて一般的でしたが、パンチカードのchadのこの用法は良い考えではありません。その断片は硬く、目を傷つけかねない鋭い角があるからです。GLSが報告するところによれば、彼はかつてMITでの結婚式に出席し、その際に彼と数人の他の客が米の代わりにchadを熱心に投げました。新郎は後で、彼と花嫁が夜のほとんどをそれを髪から取り除こうとして過ごしたとぼやいたそうです。"

#: ../../C/computer-confetti.rst:16
msgid ""
"[2001 update: this term has passed out of use for two reasons; (1) the stuff"
" it describes is now quite rare, and (2) the term :ref:`chad`\\, which was "
"half-forgotten in 1990, has enjoyed a revival. —ESR]"
msgstr ""
"[2001年更新:この用語は2つの理由で廃れました。(1) それが表す物が今やかなりまれであること、(2) 1990年には半ば忘れられていた\\ "
":ref:`chad`\\ という用語が復活を遂げたこと。——ESR]"
